commit_message:
Add service_name into PuppetConfig dict

When parsing the JSON, it is currently impossible to have unique values
per dict, e.g. neutron services sharing the same config_volume.

That patch adds the service_name into the dict so each entry can be
identified uniquely.

Input data:
{
    "data": [
        {
            "service_name": "nova_api",
            "puppet_config": {
               "config_volume": "nova",
               "step_config": "::nova",
            },
        },
        {
            "service_name": "neutron_server",
            "puppet_config": {
               "config_volume": "neutron",
               "step_config": "::neutron",
            },
        },
        {
            "service_name": "neutron_server",
        },
    ]
}

Applying the YAQL query:

Output data:
[
    {
        "config_volume": "nova",
        "service_name": "nova_api",
        "step_config": "::nova"
    },
    {
        "config_volume": "neutron",
        "service_name": "neutron_server",
        "step_config": "::neutron"
    }
]

The output is the same as before, except it now has the service_name in
each item.

